The paper focuses on image generation using GANs, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of self-supervision learning and the integration of semantic supervisory information suggest the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The scalability of the method on object classes may also suggest the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
